properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 10 at 12:18AM PST until February 10 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Sustained northeast winds 35 to 45 mph, with gusts near
55 mph expected. Local wind gusts near 90 mph are possible over
exposed ridgetops and near the Sierra Nevada crest.

* WHERE...North Kings River.

* WHEN...Until 10 PM PST Monday night.

* TIMING...The highest wind gusts are expected tonight into
Monday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging wind gusts will blow down trees and power
lines. A few power outages are likely.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Avoid power lines. Stay clear of trees.

NWSheadline: A WIND ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST MONDAY NIGHT
